Iavan Pijoos, News24Johannesburg&nbsp;- A Mpumalanga police officer will appear before the Badplaas Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Thursday for alleged dealing in rhino horn, the Hawks said. The 39-year-old constable was linked to suspects who were arrested for alleged possession of rhino horn in Badplaas on April 5, Lieutenant Dineo Sekgotodi said. The officer allegedly used a state vehicle to take the suspects to meet buyers for the horn.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.